This is just a grass. Nothing to explore.

This tapestry is torn by the elements, the image almost entirely faded. It has been placed high enough on the ruined wall that typical woodland creatures cannot reach it, but there are still a scratches and rips in its rough surface.

Given the state of the structure around it, it's clear that this tapestry is not as old as the stonework upon which it rests. Someone or something must have placed it there long after the fall of whatever once stood on this hill...
This scroll is dirty and old. Part of it crumbles at a mere touch and any writing that may have been visible on its surface has long been washed away.
This backpack, while in fair shape, no longer carries anything of use or value.
